quran[4]{c,v,t}:
  4,97,"And those the angels take, while still they are wronging themselves -- the angels will say, 'In what circumstances were you?' They will say, 'We were abased in the earth.' The angels will say, 'But was not God's earth wide, so that you might have emigrated in it?' Such men, their refuge shall be Gehenna -- an evil homecoming"
  4,98,"except the men, women, and children who, being abased, can devise nothing and are not guided to a way"
  4,99,"haply them God will yet pardon, for God is All-pardoning, All-forgiving"
  4,100,"Whoso emigrates in the way of God will find in the earth many refuges and plenty; whoso goes forth from his house an emigrant to God and His Messenger, and then death overtakes him, his wage shall have fallen on God; surely God is All-forgiving, All-compassionate"